<div class="space-y-4">
    <p>
        Internet culture has increasingly influenced contemporary art, introducing new ways to communicate ideas through images and digital media. Today, memes function as a global visual language. They move fluidly across political borders and often address sensitive topics with humor and sharp honesty.
    </p>
    <p>
        In the past, this kind of critical, idea-driven expression was often the domain of conceptual art. But conceptual work frequently relied on insider knowledge, limiting who could fully engage with it. Memes, by contrast, offer a more accessible form of communication. They reveal unexpected expressive potential, forging connections with broad audiences and bridging the gap between high art and everyday digital exchange. This shift challenges traditional art hierarchies. It opens up artistic expression to a wider public and expands who gets to participate in defining what art means in the digital age.
    </p>
</div> 